    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-08-24T00:35:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-08-24T00:35:00-05:00" n="577"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d577">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">891.711/53: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Iran</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Engert</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Teheran</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-08-24T09:00:00+03:25"
                            >August 24, 1937—9 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 9:45 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>69. Legation’s telegram No. 47, July 14, 10 a.m. I am glad to be able to report
                    that as a result of further informal representations the local post office is
                    now digging up old mail matter which was at first believed to have been
                    destroyed. The Legation and American nationals have recently been receiving
                    periodicals dated March, April, etc., 1936, and I am hopeful that more will be
                    forthcoming.</p>
                <p>Please inform Post Office Department but not for publication.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Engert</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
